            <c02 level="subseries">
               <did>
                  <unitid>Item 1</unitid>
                  <unittitle>"The Hard Shell Baptists" sermon, <unitdate>n.d.</unitdate>
                  </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>The term, "Hard-Shell Baptists" was used during the 19th century to refer to primitive, fundamentalist, uneducated Baptists. This sermon may not have originated vith the First Baptist Church of Seneca Falls, but has been filed with other Baptist material because of the title.</p>
                  <p>This is a comical, satirical
				  sermon, possibly pretend, referring to an uneducated preacher. It also satirizes other religious groups including Methodists, United Brethren, Catholics and Universalists, and their ways of attaining salvation, c. 1860</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="subseries">
               <did>
                  <unitid>Item 2</unitid>
                  <unittitle>"The Baptist Church Manual", <unitdate>1853</unitdate>.</unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Published by the American Baptist Publication Society, Philadelphia.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="subseries">
               <did>
                  <unitid>Item 3</unitid>
                  <unittitle>"The Sunday School Receiving Book," <unitdate>Nov. 1838-1850</unitdate>. </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Contains lists of pupils with date of entry, register number, parent's name, parent's occupation and character, residence, class, and remarks. There is one list for 1838-46, one for Oct. 22, 1848-1850. A list of Sunday School officers is also included. </p>
               </scopecontent>
